Hi.

Lets get this straight. 

When the time comes to use ISO directory services and X.400 O/R names
it is not going to a trivial matter of adding one more node our domain
name tree.  ISO names are completely different in concept.
The data structure and mechanism may support the ISO name system (with
clever use of what is there and some extensions), but the way names appear
to the user will be very different.

The domains COM, EDU, etc international in scope.

It is not the intent to move the current COM and EDU domains under the US
domain.

The current working throry on how to organize the US domain is by political
georgraphy, that is, State, Cities, etc.  Thoughtful suggestions will be
appreciated.

As the responsible person for the US domain i have yet to receive an
application from anyone to join it.

--jon.

